properties.areaDesc: South Laramie Range Foothills; South Laramie Range
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 16 at 2:06AM MST until February 17 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph. Patchy
blowing and drifting snow.

* WHERE...South Laramie Range and South Laramie Range Foothills.

* WHEN...Until 8 PM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Expect dangerous travel for
lightweight, high profile vehicles including camping and
tractor trailers. There will be a high risk for blowovers of
these types of vehicles. Blowing and drifting snow may cause
some slick roadways and lower visibility to develop at times.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of
58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

Call 5 1 1 or go to wyoroad.info for the latest information on
road conditions and closures.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 PM MST MONDAY
